2
00:00:02,467 --> 00:00:02,997
[tapping]

3
00:00:03,515 --> 00:00:04,821
Apple Bloom: Hear
ye, hear ye!

4
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:06,816
This meeting of the
Cutie Mark Crusaders

5
00:00:06,833 --> 00:00:08,328
is now in session.

6
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:09,675
Who wants to do roll call?

7
00:00:11,368 --> 00:00:12,938
I'm pretty sure we're all here.

8
00:00:13,229 --> 00:00:15,440
Yeah, Apple Bloom,
what's this all about?

9
00:00:15,856 --> 00:00:17,633
Oh, nothin'...

10
00:00:19,157 --> 00:00:21,115
Except this letter
from Babs Seed

11
00:00:21,132 --> 00:00:22,909
saying she's got
her cutie mark!

12
00:00:22,993 --> 00:00:24,033
WHAT?

13
00:00:24,176 --> 00:00:26,176
She says it's a
pair of scissors.

14
00:00:26,534 --> 00:00:29,048
So... she's good
at cutting stuff?

15
00:00:29,115 --> 00:00:30,265
Of course!

16
00:00:30,517 --> 00:00:32,778
She was always fussing
with her bangs and tail.

17
00:00:33,082 --> 00:00:35,494
I'll bet she grows up to
be a celebrity stylist.

18
00:00:35,772 --> 00:00:38,273
But if she spends all
her time cutting hair,

19
00:00:38,703 --> 00:00:41,006
who's gonna run the
Manehattan CMCs?

20
00:00:41,292 --> 00:00:42,400
Well, not Babs.

21
00:00:42,475 --> 00:00:44,138
She can't be a
Cutie Mark Crusader

22
00:00:44,151 --> 00:00:45,915
if she's already got
her cutie mark.

23
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:47,743
Oh, wow. I guess
you're right.

24
00:00:49,073 --> 00:00:52,160
I'm glad she's happy, but
I sure wouldn't want to be

25
00:00:52,193 --> 00:00:53,987
up to my flank in
mane hair all day.

26
00:00:54,105 --> 00:00:55,461
Can you imagine
getting stuck

27
00:00:55,486 --> 00:00:57,275
with a cutie mark
you didn't like?

28
00:00:58,437 --> 00:01:01,145
No... Or, at
least, I hadn't.

29
00:01:01,549 --> 00:01:02,694
Don't worry, Apple Bloom.

30
00:01:02,934 --> 00:01:05,317
Most of your family has
apple related cutie marks.

31
00:01:05,532 --> 00:01:06,656
I bet yours will be too.

32
00:01:06,909 --> 00:01:08,762
And what's not to
like about apples?

33
00:01:08,930 --> 00:01:12,395
There's the core, and sour
apples, and rotten apples,

34
00:01:12,412 --> 00:01:14,197
and apples with worms in them...

35
00:01:15,536 --> 00:01:16,248
What?

36
00:01:16,374 --> 00:01:17,305
Not helping.

37
00:01:27,321 --> 00:01:32,320
HOH Subtitles by YayPonies
We have muffins!
http://main.yayponies.eu

38
00:01:52,246 --> 00:01:54,313
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39
00:01:59,709 --> 00:02:01,267
Apple Bloom: I guess I
just spent so much time

40
00:02:01,284 --> 00:02:03,141
worrying about how to
get a cutie mark,

41
00:02:03,726 --> 00:02:06,185
I never even thought about
what would happen after.

42
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:08,698
There's just so many
things I never considered.

43
00:02:09,915 --> 00:02:11,844
I'm sure there are, but
you don't need to--

44
00:02:11,890 --> 00:02:13,280
What if I finally
get my cutie mark

45
00:02:13,301 --> 00:02:14,286
and I don't like it?

46
00:02:14,581 --> 00:02:16,858
What if I get my cutie
mark and nopony likes me?

47
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:18,273
Well, that's just ridicul--

48
00:02:18,298 --> 00:02:19,915
What if the Crusaders
drift apart?

49
00:02:20,176 --> 00:02:23,406
I mean, we won't really be the
Cutie Mark Crusaders anymore.

50
00:02:24,648 --> 00:02:25,882
What if it's not an apple?

51
00:02:25,983 --> 00:02:26,938
Will I have to move out?

52
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:28,341
Where will I live?

53
00:02:28,412 --> 00:02:30,421
All right. That's
enough, sugar cube.

54
00:02:30,690 --> 00:02:33,861
Those are way too many questions
to answer all in one night.

55
00:02:34,029 --> 00:02:34,425
But--

56
00:02:34,496 --> 00:02:36,825
And nopony's gonna
make you move out.

57
00:02:37,077 --> 00:02:38,804
Are you sure, Applejack?

58
00:02:39,221 --> 00:02:40,581
Of course I'm sure.

59
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:41,978
Now get some sleep.

60
00:02:42,404 --> 00:02:43,250
You'll see.

61
00:02:43,553 --> 00:02:45,351
Everything'll be
better in the morning.

62
00:02:46,088 --> 00:02:49,701
<i> ♪ Hush now little sister,</i>
<i>you're loved by all you know, ♪</i>

63
00:02:50,029 --> 00:02:51,789
<i> ♪ you'll never lose</i>
<i> their friendship, ♪</i>

64
00:02:51,861 --> 00:02:53,494
<i> ♪ no matter where you go. ♪</i>

65
00:02:53,932 --> 00:02:58,080
<i>♪ There ain't no call to worry,</i>
<i> so don't you cry or fret, ♪</i>

66
00:02:58,437 --> 00:03:02,753
<i> ♪ a cutie mark won't change</i>
<i> you, no matter what you get. ♪</i>

67
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,406
[yawn]

68
00:03:07,701 --> 00:03:09,258
No matter what I get.

69
00:03:12,620 --> 00:03:19,120
[snoring]

70
00:03:19,191 --> 00:03:21,465
[rooster crows]

71
00:03:24,172 --> 00:03:25,385
Hoo whee!

72
00:03:25,503 --> 00:03:27,027
Nothing like a
good night's sleep.

73
00:03:27,296 --> 00:03:28,261
Applejack: Breakfast!

74
00:03:31,317 --> 00:03:32,534
You were right, Applejack.

75
00:03:32,710 --> 00:03:34,193
I feel much better.

76
00:03:34,517 --> 00:03:36,783
I don't know what I was so
worried about last night.

77
00:03:37,174 --> 00:03:38,635
See? Now, what did
I tell you?

78
00:03:39,061 --> 00:03:40,938
A good night's sleep'll
fix just about an--

79
00:03:42,816 --> 00:03:45,174
Well, no wonder you
were so worked up.

80
00:03:45,482 --> 00:03:46,008
What?

81
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:47,701
What is it?

82
00:03:48,058 --> 00:03:50,985
Looks like somepony
got her cutie mark!

83
00:03:52,673 --> 00:03:53,755
I can't believe it.

84
00:03:53,978 --> 00:03:55,658
I got my cutie mark.

85
00:03:57,894 --> 00:03:59,246
I got my cutie mark!

86
00:03:59,856 --> 00:04:02,378
I GOT MY CUTIE MARK!

87
00:04:06,016 --> 00:04:09,166
Wait till I tell the others
that my cutie mark is a, a...

88
00:04:10,741 --> 00:04:11,406
What is it?

89
00:04:11,861 --> 00:04:14,168
I have no idea
what it means.

90
00:04:14,543 --> 00:04:16,016
Old man voice: I
know what it means.

91
00:04:21,658 --> 00:04:23,583
It means I can retire.

92
00:04:23,621 --> 00:04:24,951
Ha hoo!

93
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:28,934
Infestations?

94
00:04:29,376 --> 00:04:31,115
You mean, like, Parasprites?

95
00:04:31,861 --> 00:04:35,642
Please. Any pony with a trombone
can get rid of Parasprites.

96
00:04:35,827 --> 00:04:38,029
I'm talking about
the serious stuff.

97
00:04:38,206 --> 00:04:41,040
You ever hear of Twittermites?

98
00:04:41,162 --> 00:04:42,168
[thunder]

99
00:04:43,566 --> 00:04:44,690
Twittermites?

100
00:04:46,437 --> 00:04:49,309
Pest Ponies like you and me are
the only things keeping these

101
00:04:49,338 --> 00:04:52,341
live wires from destroying
half of Equestria.

102
00:04:52,867 --> 00:04:53,869
Pest Ponies?

103
00:04:54,105 --> 00:04:55,726
It's no easy trade.

104
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,837
Even the best of us
yearns for the day

105
00:04:58,854 --> 00:05:01,473
they can move on to
greener pastures.

106
00:05:01,827 --> 00:05:06,033
And now that you're here to take
over, my day has finally come.

107
00:05:06,197 --> 00:05:07,258
Take over?

108
00:05:07,671 --> 00:05:09,743
You're gonna need to stop
repeating everything I say

109
00:05:09,764 --> 00:05:11,355
and pay attention if you
want to learn anything.

110
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:13,061
I'm sorry.

111
00:05:13,385 --> 00:05:15,962
I guess this just wasn't
what I was expecting.

112
00:05:16,997 --> 00:05:19,385
Don't worry, with a
cutie mark like that,

113
00:05:19,448 --> 00:05:21,048
I'm sure you've got the touch.

114
00:05:21,309 --> 00:05:21,970
The touch?

115
00:05:22,282 --> 00:05:23,237
Oh. Sorry.

116
00:05:27,629 --> 00:05:30,046
Now you're gonna
need to be quick.

117
00:05:30,383 --> 00:05:34,505
Once these things get out,
it can get pretty shocking.

118
00:05:35,957 --> 00:05:38,248
[buzzing]

119
00:05:38,421 --> 00:05:38,972
Wait.

120
00:05:39,562 --> 00:05:40,328
What do you mean?

121
00:05:40,618 --> 00:05:41,267
OUCH!

122
00:05:41,583 --> 00:05:43,229
Ha ha! Told ya!

123
00:05:43,402 --> 00:05:44,960
And the farther
apart they spread,

124
00:05:44,993 --> 00:05:47,035
the more powerful
these jolts'll get.

125
00:05:48,454 --> 00:05:49,482
[zap]

126
00:05:50,410 --> 00:05:51,410
What do I do?

127
00:05:51,646 --> 00:05:53,048
Call them back,
of course.

128
00:05:54,416 --> 00:05:55,722
Twittermites!

129
00:05:56,294 --> 00:05:57,157
[whistle]

130
00:05:57,246 --> 00:05:58,012
Here!

131
00:05:58,513 --> 00:06:00,690
[buzzing]

132
00:06:05,389 --> 00:06:06,648
Twittermites!

133
00:06:14,395 --> 00:06:16,480
Bug, bug, bug,
bug, bug, bug, bug!

134
00:06:20,753 --> 00:06:23,574
Well, it looks like
you're all set.

135
00:06:23,802 --> 00:06:25,191
Drop me a note sometime

136
00:06:25,216 --> 00:06:27,376
at the Piney Shade
retirement community.

137
00:06:27,747 --> 00:06:28,711
Now hold on...

138
00:06:28,976 --> 00:06:31,128
I'm sure this job
is real important,

139
00:06:31,195 --> 00:06:34,378
but I don't think I wanna call
bugs for the rest of my life.

140
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:36,829
Hey, where'd he go?

141
00:06:37,435 --> 00:06:38,888
Well, well, well.

142
00:06:39,107 --> 00:06:41,591
Look at the new Bug Pony.

143
00:06:41,827 --> 00:06:43,305
It's Pest Pony.

144
00:06:44,206 --> 00:06:46,315
It sure is.

145
00:06:46,446 --> 00:06:47,128
Ew!

146
00:06:47,541 --> 00:06:51,730
I might have known you'd end up
with the worst cutie mark ever.

147
00:06:51,802 --> 00:06:56,290
[nasty laughter]

148
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:58,071
But look on the bright side.

149
00:06:58,210 --> 00:07:02,395
Whenever you need a friend, you
can just go out and catch one.

150
00:07:02,677 --> 00:07:04,033
That's not funny.

151
00:07:04,206 --> 00:07:07,191
HEEEERE friend, friend,
friend, friend, friend...

152
00:07:07,229 --> 00:07:08,269
Stop it.

153
00:07:08,690 --> 00:07:10,711
Here, bug! Here, bug!

154
00:07:10,757 --> 00:07:12,286
Will you be my friend, bug?

155
00:07:12,345 --> 00:07:14,745
Because nopony else will!

156
00:07:14,825 --> 00:07:15,595
Ha ha ha!

157
00:07:15,629 --> 00:07:16,189
You know what?

158
00:07:16,328 --> 00:07:17,865
My cutie mark isn't the worst.

159
00:07:18,029 --> 00:07:19,052
You two are!

160
00:07:20,429 --> 00:07:25,128
[hooting laughter]

161
00:07:31,035 --> 00:07:33,326
I hate to think that
Diamond Tiara is right,

162
00:07:33,701 --> 00:07:36,812
but this cutie mark sure
isn't what I was hoping for.

163
00:07:37,326 --> 00:07:40,311
[echo voice] Why should you
have to keep it, then?

164
00:07:40,509 --> 00:07:41,435
Who's there?

165
00:07:42,113 --> 00:07:43,258
What do you mean?

166
00:07:46,391 --> 00:07:50,749
If your cutie mark bothers
you so much, get rid of it.

167
00:07:52,109 --> 00:07:53,755
Well, if you know
how to wave a hoof

168
00:07:53,772 --> 00:07:57,040
and erase a terrible cutie
mark, you go right ahead.

169
00:07:57,532 --> 00:08:00,235
As easily said as done.

170
00:08:00,277 --> 00:08:03,650
[whistling wind]

171
00:08:05,710 --> 00:08:08,985
Huh. Now that is
some serious magic.

172
00:08:13,549 --> 00:08:15,490
[screams]

173
00:08:15,528 --> 00:08:17,646
Hey, where's everypony going?

174
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:22,033
[panicked screams]

175
00:08:22,206 --> 00:08:23,738
Mayor, what's going on!

176
00:08:24,008 --> 00:08:24,732
Apple Bloom!

177
00:08:24,846 --> 00:08:26,804
You've got to get your
family out of town!

178
00:08:31,595 --> 00:08:33,208
Twittermites!

179
00:08:34,914 --> 00:08:36,014
[gasp]

180
00:08:37,023 --> 00:08:41,680
♪♪

181
00:08:41,835 --> 00:08:43,098
Twittermites!

182
00:08:44,863 --> 00:08:46,837
Heeeere, bug, bug,
bug, bug, bug!

183
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,286
[zap]

184
00:08:50,749 --> 00:08:51,541
Here, bug!

185
00:08:51,827 --> 00:08:59,663
♪♪

186
00:09:00,084 --> 00:09:01,423
Come on here!

187
00:09:02,884 --> 00:09:05,696
Apple Bloom, what in
tarnation are you doing?

188
00:09:05,907 --> 00:09:08,749
I'm trying to stop the
infestation, of course!

189
00:09:09,145 --> 00:09:10,943
Only a Pest Pony can do that!

190
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:14,404
♪♪

191
00:09:14,442 --> 00:09:15,317
Now come on.

192
00:09:15,465 --> 00:09:16,648
We've gotta skedaddle!

193
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:19,515
♪♪

194
00:09:19,650 --> 00:09:21,343
But I've got to do something!

195
00:09:22,054 --> 00:09:23,473
Are you crazy?

196
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:28,589
♪♪

197
00:09:28,736 --> 00:09:30,720
[explosion]

198
00:09:41,082 --> 00:09:41,667
AAAAAHHH!

199
00:09:41,701 --> 00:09:43,920
[rooster crows]

200
00:09:47,461 --> 00:09:48,547
Hoo whee!

201
00:09:48,884 --> 00:09:50,816
That's what I call
a nightmare!

202
00:09:51,216 --> 00:09:52,395
It seemed so real.

203
00:09:52,724 --> 00:09:54,395
Applejack: Breakfast!

204
00:09:57,136 --> 00:10:00,437
Applejack, you are not gonna
believe the dream I just had.

205
00:10:00,715 --> 00:10:02,720
I guess I needed more
sleep than I thought.

206
00:10:03,061 --> 00:10:04,728
See? Now, what did
I tell you?

207
00:10:04,896 --> 00:10:06,762
A good night's sleep
will fix just abou--

208
00:10:07,418 --> 00:10:07,915
[gasp]

209
00:10:08,290 --> 00:10:10,778
Well, no wonder you
were so worked up.

210
00:10:11,023 --> 00:10:11,650
What?

211
00:10:11,730 --> 00:10:14,631
Looks like somepony
got her cutie mark!

212
00:10:14,846 --> 00:10:15,814
Again?

213
00:10:16,155 --> 00:10:17,802
I mean, I did?

214
00:10:18,357 --> 00:10:19,709
Woohoo!

215
00:10:20,244 --> 00:10:21,360
Potion making!

216
00:10:21,747 --> 00:10:23,212
Now that's more like it!

217
00:10:23,452 --> 00:10:24,534
More like what?

218
00:10:25,178 --> 00:10:25,869
Never mind.

219
00:10:26,206 --> 00:10:28,273
I'm just glad Princess
Twilight's lessons

220
00:10:28,303 --> 00:10:29,410
finally paid off.

221
00:10:29,608 --> 00:10:31,734
I expect you want to run
off to the clubhouse

222
00:10:31,751 --> 00:10:33,823
and tell your friends all
about your new cutie mark.

223
00:10:34,181 --> 00:10:36,816
But before you go, make
sure you do all your--

224
00:10:39,389 --> 00:10:40,181
--chores?

225
00:10:41,797 --> 00:10:42,656
[clang]

226
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:44,762
Woo hoo!

227
00:10:46,113 --> 00:10:47,200
Why all the excitement?

228
00:10:47,503 --> 00:10:48,909
Yeah. What's going on?

229
00:10:49,498 --> 00:10:51,435
Oh, nothin'.

230
00:10:52,180 --> 00:10:54,804
Except this brand
new cutie mark!

231
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:57,094
Wow!
That's amazing!

232
00:10:57,115 --> 00:10:58,008
Whoo hoo!

233
00:10:58,193 --> 00:10:59,987
[excited shouts]

234
00:11:00,130 --> 00:11:02,298
I don't suppose either
of you got yours?

235
00:11:02,631 --> 00:11:03,385
Nope.

236
00:11:03,646 --> 00:11:04,715
Me neither.

237
00:11:05,216 --> 00:11:06,231
I know it's silly but,

238
00:11:06,252 --> 00:11:08,938
I always hoped we'd get our
cutie marks together.

239
00:11:09,284 --> 00:11:10,269
Me too.

240
00:11:10,606 --> 00:11:12,606
But I'm still super
excited for you!

241
00:11:12,736 --> 00:11:14,058
Absolutely!

242
00:11:15,174 --> 00:11:15,970
I know!

243
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,206
Let's call this
meeting to order.

244
00:11:18,387 --> 00:11:20,105
I'm sure the three
of us can figure out

245
00:11:20,122 --> 00:11:22,294
how to get two
more cutie marks!

246
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:24,800
Um...yeah.

247
00:11:25,170 --> 00:11:26,644
The thing is...

248
00:11:26,972 --> 00:11:27,494
What?

249
00:11:27,886 --> 00:11:30,661
Well, you can't be a
Cutie Mark Crusader

250
00:11:30,715 --> 00:11:33,090
if you've already got
your cutie mark.

251
00:11:33,545 --> 00:11:35,002
Oh. Yeah.

252
00:11:35,229 --> 00:11:36,471
Just like Babs Seed.

253
00:11:37,048 --> 00:11:38,854
Well, I can just sit
quietly in the corner

254
00:11:38,871 --> 00:11:40,812
while you two figure out
what you're gonna do.

255
00:11:41,124 --> 00:11:44,703
Well, technically, the clubhouse
is for Crusaders only.

256
00:11:46,214 --> 00:11:46,715
Oh.

257
00:11:46,901 --> 00:11:47,469
Right.

258
00:11:48,282 --> 00:11:50,522
I guess I should just
come back later, then?

259
00:11:50,749 --> 00:11:51,254
Why?

260
00:11:51,557 --> 00:11:53,852
I mean, you can't
come in then either.

261
00:11:54,197 --> 00:11:54,694
Oh.

262
00:11:55,343 --> 00:11:56,261
Rules are rules.

263
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:59,427
I don't even think we're
still supposed to be friends.

264
00:11:59,490 --> 00:12:00,029
[close]

265
00:12:00,421 --> 00:12:00,905
What?

266
00:12:06,273 --> 00:12:07,730
Sweetie Belle?

267
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,195
Scootaloo?

268
00:12:09,461 --> 00:12:11,578
Come on, fillies!
This isn't funny.

269
00:12:14,652 --> 00:12:17,343
[echo] More trouble
with cutie marks?

270
00:12:19,023 --> 00:12:19,709
No.

271
00:12:20,109 --> 00:12:21,663
I mean, yeah.

272
00:12:21,684 --> 00:12:22,576
I mean...

273
00:12:22,955 --> 00:12:26,058
Well, I got mine, but my
friends didn't get theirs

274
00:12:26,088 --> 00:12:27,818
and now there's all
kinds of trouble.

275
00:12:28,336 --> 00:12:31,098
<i> Sounds to me like cutie</i>
<i> marks and trouble</i>

276
00:12:31,111 --> 00:12:34,884
<i> are two peas in</i>
<i> the same pod.</i>

277
00:12:35,305 --> 00:12:36,362
I guess so.

278
00:12:36,787 --> 00:12:38,964
I mean, if I was a
blank flank again,

279
00:12:39,073 --> 00:12:40,522
there wouldn't be a problem.

280
00:12:41,018 --> 00:12:43,313
<i> Your wish is my command.</i>

281
00:12:43,658 --> 00:12:47,743
<i> [whoosh]</i>

282
00:12:51,911 --> 00:12:52,858
Hey, Apple Bloom.

283
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:54,042
Why'd you want to meet here?

284
00:12:55,713 --> 00:12:58,576
Well, us blankflanks
have to meet somewhere!

285
00:12:59,541 --> 00:13:01,397
Um... actually,
Apple Bloom,

286
00:13:01,705 --> 00:13:03,768
we both sort of got
our cutie marks.

287
00:13:04,564 --> 00:13:05,637
You did?

288
00:13:06,951 --> 00:13:07,882
What are they?

289
00:13:08,345 --> 00:13:11,103
Oh, we don't have time
to go into all that.

290
00:13:11,818 --> 00:13:14,753
And we certainly don't have time
to hang out in an old clubhouse.

291
00:13:14,875 --> 00:13:17,107
Yeah. We've got
responsibilities now.

292
00:13:17,431 --> 00:13:19,023
But, maybe we'll see you later.

293
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:20,370
Much later.

294
00:13:20,538 --> 00:13:21,098
Wait!

295
00:13:21,326 --> 00:13:22,033
Hold on!

296
00:13:22,256 --> 00:13:23,507
I can get my cutie mark back.

297
00:13:23,789 --> 00:13:24,593
I think.

298
00:13:25,427 --> 00:13:27,242
I mean, I got it once, right?

299
00:13:28,025 --> 00:13:29,528
Just wait a second!

300
00:13:31,381 --> 00:13:34,000
No!

301
00:13:34,698 --> 00:13:37,178
[rooster crows]

302
00:13:42,884 --> 00:13:45,658
What in Equestria is going on?

303
00:13:45,869 --> 00:13:47,482
Applejack: Breakfast!

304
00:13:47,810 --> 00:13:51,587
I'm not so sure sleep is the
cure-all Applejack thinks it is.

305
00:13:53,764 --> 00:13:55,410
Uh... Applejack?

306
00:13:55,734 --> 00:13:58,593
I know you said sleep is
supposed to make me feel better,

307
00:13:58,635 --> 00:14:01,667
but I'm pretty sure it's
making me feel worse.

308
00:14:02,075 --> 00:14:03,688
See? Now, what did
I tell you?

309
00:14:03,970 --> 00:14:05,275
A good night's
sleep will fix--

310
00:14:06,370 --> 00:14:08,981
Well, no wonder you
were so worked up.

311
00:14:10,345 --> 00:14:11,886
Didn't you hear what I said?

312
00:14:12,029 --> 00:14:12,871
I was trying to--

313
00:14:12,896 --> 00:14:16,707
Well, what do
we have here?

314
00:14:16,955 --> 00:14:17,873
What is it, Granny?

315
00:14:18,109 --> 00:14:18,783
What's wrong?

316
00:14:19,225 --> 00:14:20,694
Oh, nothin'.

317
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:22,202
Right, Applejack?

318
00:14:22,736 --> 00:14:23,658
Right.

319
00:14:23,865 --> 00:14:25,258
Nothin' at all.

320
00:14:25,490 --> 00:14:26,635
Right, Big Mac?

321
00:14:28,943 --> 00:14:30,446
Truth is, Apple Bloom...

322
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,690
it's your cutie mark.

323
00:14:33,006 --> 00:14:33,865
Eeyup.

324
00:14:34,429 --> 00:14:35,313
Oh, no.

325
00:14:35,575 --> 00:14:36,641
What is it now?

326
00:14:42,012 --> 00:14:43,650
Well, I'll tell
you what it ain't.

327
00:14:44,126 --> 00:14:45,987
It ain't no apple!

328
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,334
Nnope!

329
00:14:47,671 --> 00:14:48,168
What?

330
00:14:48,589 --> 00:14:52,800
And we don't have
room for non-Apples!

331
00:14:52,964 --> 00:14:53,848
Nnope!

332
00:14:54,181 --> 00:14:55,962
Time for you
to mosey on.

333
00:14:56,353 --> 00:14:57,789
You can't stay here.

334
00:14:58,134 --> 00:14:59,726
But this is my home.

335
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:05,229
Oh, and you're gonna
have to change your name.

336
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,402
Eeyup!

337
00:15:08,151 --> 00:15:11,107
I think just "Bloom"
has a nice ring to it,

338
00:15:11,473 --> 00:15:13,343
don't you, Applejack?

339
00:15:13,414 --> 00:15:14,391
Eeyup!

340
00:15:18,623 --> 00:15:22,732
Nooooooo!

341
00:15:27,149 --> 00:15:27,701
[grunt]

342
00:15:28,661 --> 00:15:31,129
[rooster crows]

343
00:15:31,381 --> 00:15:31,991
All right.

344
00:15:32,311 --> 00:15:34,698
This is getting ridiculous.

345
00:15:43,389 --> 00:15:44,261
Hoo whee!

346
00:15:44,442 --> 00:15:47,414
I never thought I'd be so
happy to not get a cutie mark.

347
00:15:47,911 --> 00:15:48,753
What the--?

348
00:15:58,126 --> 00:15:59,132
ARGH!

349
00:15:59,351 --> 00:16:02,450
I don't want to see another
cutie mark as long as I live!

350
00:16:07,726 --> 00:16:09,941
<i> [echo] Back so soon?</i>

351
00:16:10,429 --> 00:16:13,675
All right, whoever you are, I
don't know what spell you went

352
00:16:13,751 --> 00:16:17,077
and cast on me but I want
it to stop right now!

353
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:19,427
<i> I didn't cast a spell.</i>

354
00:16:19,444 --> 00:16:21,873
<i> On you or anypony else.</i>

355
00:16:22,332 --> 00:16:24,821
<i> I only did what you wanted.</i>

356
00:16:24,905 --> 00:16:26,378
Agh!

357
00:16:26,854 --> 00:16:29,957
Why would I want you to
torment me with nightmares?

358
00:16:30,252 --> 00:16:33,309
<i> You didn't want to</i>
<i> catch bugs and I helped.</i>

359
00:16:33,629 --> 00:16:36,505
<i> You didn't want to lose</i>
<i> friends and I helped.</i>

360
00:16:36,846 --> 00:16:39,528
<i> If there's a problem</i>
<i> with your family,</i>

361
00:16:39,658 --> 00:16:42,214
<i> I'm sure I can</i>
<i> help with that too.</i>

362
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:44,189
I don't want your help.

363
00:16:44,555 --> 00:16:46,307
Just get away from me!

364
00:16:47,435 --> 00:16:51,082
Oh, Apple Bloom, you can't get
away from your own shadow.

365
00:17:00,412 --> 00:17:01,423
Princess Luna!

366
00:17:01,701 --> 00:17:02,513
My shadow?

367
00:17:02,770 --> 00:17:03,566
What do you mean?

368
00:17:12,230 --> 00:17:13,237
It's just me?

369
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:16,269
You mean I've been doing
all this to myself?

370
00:17:16,560 --> 00:17:17,760
<i> Of course, Apple Bloom.</i>

371
00:17:18,298 --> 00:17:19,322
<i> It's your dream.</i>

372
00:17:20,357 --> 00:17:23,288
If I've been dreaming this whole
time, why don't I just wake up?

373
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:26,050
<i> Sometimes we can worry</i>
<i> about a thing so much,</i>

374
00:17:26,071 --> 00:17:29,145
<i> the fear can make us feel like</i>
<i> we're trapped in a nightmare.</i>

375
00:17:34,669 --> 00:17:36,404
I don't suppose
there's anything

376
00:17:36,421 --> 00:17:38,715
you're particularly
afraid of, is there?

377
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:40,383
Yeah.

378
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,898
I guess I'm pretty worried
about getting my cutie mark.

379
00:17:44,190 --> 00:17:47,490
Well, that is the same as
worrying about who you are.

380
00:17:48,029 --> 00:17:49,692
That is all a cutie mark is.

381
00:17:50,054 --> 00:17:51,953
If you cannot
accept who you are,

382
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:54,488
your life might seem
like a bad dream.

383
00:17:55,498 --> 00:17:59,915
But, if I like who I am, do you
think other ponies will too?

384
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:02,492
Of course.

385
00:18:04,117 --> 00:18:06,715
Then it doesn't matter
what my cutie mark is!

386
00:18:07,317 --> 00:18:08,404
Indeed.

387
00:18:08,703 --> 00:18:10,320
But that's so simple.

388
00:18:10,543 --> 00:18:12,829
I must be the only
pony in the universe

389
00:18:12,846 --> 00:18:14,635
this worried about
her cutie mark.

390
00:18:15,035 --> 00:18:17,448
Oh, I wouldn't say that.

391
00:18:18,130 --> 00:18:19,128
[whoosh]

392
00:18:20,976 --> 00:18:26,395
♪♪

393
00:18:30,896 --> 00:18:31,781
[sigh]

394
00:18:31,818 --> 00:19:04,294
♪♪

395
00:19:04,442 --> 00:19:09,461
Aaaaahh!

396
00:19:09,957 --> 00:19:12,058
♪♪

397
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:15,094
[struggling grunts]

398
00:19:16,450 --> 00:19:19,309
Scootaloo and Sweetie Belle
are having nightmares too?

399
00:19:19,663 --> 00:19:21,431
It's been a busy
night for us all,

400
00:19:21,941 --> 00:19:24,433
but I think it's time
to bring it to a close.

401
00:19:30,543 --> 00:19:32,075
Princess Luna!

402
00:19:32,560 --> 00:19:34,720
I know you've all had a
lot on your minds tonight,

403
00:19:35,237 --> 00:19:38,054
but I think Apple Bloom has
something she'd like to share

404
00:19:38,075 --> 00:19:39,052
before you wake.

405
00:19:39,877 --> 00:19:40,930
We're still asleep?

406
00:19:41,861 --> 00:19:42,997
Cool!

407
00:19:46,795 --> 00:19:49,583
Well, I guess I should
call this dream meeting

408
00:19:49,608 --> 00:19:51,713
of the Cutie Mark
Crusaders to order.

409
00:19:53,183 --> 00:19:55,621
I know we all got pretty
anxious when we found out

410
00:19:55,667 --> 00:19:57,157
Babs got her cutie mark.

411
00:19:57,372 --> 00:20:00,096
But I, for one, don't wanna
have nightmares every night

412
00:20:00,117 --> 00:20:01,709
from now until we get ours.

413
00:20:01,928 --> 00:20:02,778
Me neither.

414
00:20:03,203 --> 00:20:04,969
And even though we're
all a little scared,

415
00:20:05,023 --> 00:20:06,972
a cutie mark won't
change who we are

416
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:08,833
or how everypony
feels about us.

417
00:20:09,111 --> 00:20:11,528
It's lucky we're all
scared of the same things.

418
00:20:11,726 --> 00:20:13,532
That way we can help
and remind each other

419
00:20:13,557 --> 00:20:14,854
to just be who we are.

420
00:20:15,418 --> 00:20:16,387
And when the day comes

421
00:20:16,404 --> 00:20:18,581
that you all finally
get your cutie marks,

422
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:20,938
you can be sure they'll
fit you to a tee.

423
00:20:21,343 --> 00:20:22,534
Exactly.

424
00:20:23,027 --> 00:20:25,343
Do you fillies think that
Babs is worried or scared

425
00:20:25,368 --> 00:20:26,437
about some of this stuff?

426
00:20:27,385 --> 00:20:28,063
I know!

427
00:20:28,286 --> 00:20:30,669
Let's put together a
care package for her!

428
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:32,833
That way she'll know
she isn't alone!

429
00:20:33,288 --> 00:20:34,332
We wouldn't want
her to think

430
00:20:34,357 --> 00:20:36,189
that just because she
isn't a Crusader,

431
00:20:36,412 --> 00:20:38,004
we can't still be friends.

432
00:20:39,183 --> 00:20:40,210
But...

433
00:20:40,804 --> 00:20:42,888
maybe we should wait
until we wake up.

434
00:20:43,162 --> 00:20:43,978
Good idea.

435
00:20:48,896 --> 00:20:49,423
[gasp]

436
00:20:49,701 --> 00:20:51,435
[rooster crows]

437
00:20:51,722 --> 00:20:54,580
♪♪

438
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:55,911
[sigh]

439
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:05,667
<i>♪ There ain't no call to worry,</i>
<i> so don't you cry or fret... ♪</i>

440
00:21:06,362 --> 00:21:10,265
<i> ♪ A cutie mark won't change</i>
<i> me, no matter what I get! ♪</i>

441
00:21:10,741 --> 00:21:13,330
Well, it sure looks like
somepony is feeling better.

442
00:21:14,715 --> 00:21:16,842
You have no idea.

443
00:21:17,267 --> 00:21:19,313
See? Now, what did
I tell ya?

444
00:21:19,751 --> 00:21:22,467
A good night's sleep cures
just about everything.

445
00:21:23,536 --> 00:21:24,741
I guess so...

446
00:21:25,149 --> 00:21:28,193
I just wish it hadn't
been so exhausting.

